data.title: Maria Leopoldine of Austria
data.text:
Archduchess Maria Leopoldine of Austria (6 April 1632 – 7 August 1649) was by birth Archduchess of Austria and member of the Tyrolese branch of the House of Habsburg and by marriage the second wife of her first cousin, Ferdinand III, Holy Roman Emperor. As such, she was Empress of the Holy Roman Empire, German Queen and Queen consort of Hungary and Bohemia. She died in childbirth.

Marriage[edit]

On 2 July 1648, she married Ferdinand III, Holy Roman Emperor.

Issue[edit]

Archduke Karl Joseph of Austria (7 August 1649 – 27 January 1664) never married.
